<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-10-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-10-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="567" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d567">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Combs</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Lima</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-10-18"><hi rend="italic">October 18,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Minister of Ecuador at Lima has formally by note presented proposition
                            for direct negotiations. Minister for foreign affairs of Peru will
                            probably decline to consider it or any proposition, relying on mediators
                            for solution.</p>
                        <p>It is thought Ecuador will base on this refusal a renunciation of
                            arbitration treaty of 1887.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Combs.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>